From: NextOS <noreply@archr>
Date: Mon, 18 May 2026 00:55:00 -0300
Subject: [PATCH] mathops_arm: vcvtaq_s32_f32 is AArch64-only

ARM 32-bit armv8-a NEON does NOT have vcvtaq_s32_f32 (AArch64 intrinsic).
Original check `__ARM_ARCH >= 8` matches ARMv8-A 32-bit and tries to use it,
causing implicit-declaration error on GCC 16.1.0 / 32-bit ARM target.

Restrict to true AArch64 only.
---
 celt/arm/mathops_arm.h | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/celt/arm/mathops_arm.h b/celt/arm/mathops_arm.h
index abcd123..def4567 100644
--- a/celt/arm/mathops_arm.h
+++ b/celt/arm/mathops_arm.h
@@ -38,7 +38,7 @@
 
 static inline int32x4_t vroundf(float32x4_t x)
 {
-#  if defined(__aarch64__) || (defined(__ARM_ARCH) && __ARM_ARCH >= 8)
+#  if defined(__aarch64__)
     return vcvtaq_s32_f32(x);
 #  else
     uint32x4_t sign = vandq_u32(vreinterpretq_u32_f32(x), vdupq_n_u32(0x80000000));
